title: You get more than what you pay for
body: I got this headphones a couple of months ago and since then they've become my most used ones. These headphones are incredibly good. The sound is completely comparable with a highly priced pair of headphones. The bass is good. The sound isolation is not good tho since I can still hear noise around me when I use them, but is barely needed compared to the quality of the sound when playing music. I could notice sounds and instruments in songs that I've never noticed before with other headphones. And these are really good to watch movies.They are compatible with every music/sound device that I own like my laptop, phone, mp3 player and radio.The design is very comfortable and the quality of the material is acceptable. I like the way you can easily fold them to make them fit in your backpack or in a pouch for protection. As soon as I opened the box I put them in my head and I could notice that they are very strong and thanks to the material they are made of they adjust to your head very easily. I like how firm these are after a couple of hours wearing them while doing chores they still in place. They feel as equally comfortable around your neck as in your head.The quality of the cable is very good and it's made with a very strong material which is always one of the specs I look the most when buying headphones. You won't need to worry about them breaking only about the tangles. I do not like the "L" shape jack because I can't connect them on my cellphone while it has a cover on and I think these would be way better with a mic added.But overall they are really good and you definitely get more than what you pay for.

title: Excellent Value, Loud and Clear!
body: I was thinking  about spending around a hundred bucks on a set of headphones, because I was doing  some work on my computer where the sound reproduction was fairly important.  The earbuds I had just weren't cutting it.  And my previous headphones had a cord ripped out a couple months ago.  Sony was not on the list I was considering.  But I couldn't make up my mind between the Sennheisers, Audio-Technicas, and Shures, though I was leaning towards the Shures, having had an excellent pair previously.  While I was reading specs and reviews, I noticed these, and they had four and a half stars, and cost $16.  I figured, that's less than the difference in price between the ones I was looking at, so what the heck?  I always need a pair of decent ones for when I'm doing stuff outside, and I can't afford to use a hundred dollar pair that might get destroyed like the last ones.  The impedance is only 24 ohms, so they'll be plenty loud (32 ohms is fairly standard these days, which gives you less volume.  The lower the ohms, the higher the volume for the same amount of voltage.)  The frequency response is listed as 12-22,000 Hz.  Most cheap headphones and earbuds list 20-20,000 Hz, which is about the range of human hearing, and that is usually an exaggeration on their part.  In any case, the Sony MDRZX100s, while certainly not as good as the expensive Shures I  used to have, are a great buy for the money.  The sound is clear enough for what I needed, and while I still look forward to getting some audiophile phones, I am in no hurry anymore.  These are very adequate.  I would have preferred a longer cord (this is about 4 feet).  They are lightweight and very comfortable on my head for hours at a time, and right and left are clearly marked.  By the way, you will likely do less damage to your hearing using headphones than earbuds.  People tend to listen to speakers at a lower volume, measured in the ear canal, than headphones, and to earbuds loudest of all.

title: Great value for the price, reliable everyday headphones, good sound quality for their price range
body: One of the best and most reliable headphones in their price range. I have purchased two pairs now in the last few years, with careful use these can easily last you over a year. With somewhat rough usage, these headphones can withstand a fair bit of wear and tear before damage becomes visible. The sound quality is some of the best I have experienced with headphones under $20, you can get a fair bit of bass and easily enough volume to block out the noise around you without blowing out your ears.

title: it does a better job than your average in-ear buds
body: Affordable and decent quality for over the ear headphones. I wanted something to listen to music while on flights or in noisy cafes to do homework. While these headphones don't block out all of the outside noise, it does a better job than your average in-ear buds. I also like to take these when I'm flying as they are comfortable and provide good quality (blocks out a good amount of the flying noise).
